modules.description: This module implements an Adaptive Radix Tree (ART) for efficient in-memory indexing, supporting fast insertions, deletions, and lookups on string keys. It provides ordered key-value storage with operations like range scans, prefix searches, and ordered traversal via `iter`, `minimum`, and `maximum`. Concrete use cases include high-performance in-memory databases, routing tables, and auto-complete systems where dynamic key management and ordered access are critical.
